# Template for NextJS environment variables.

# For local development, copy this file, rename it to .env.local, and fill in values.
# When deploying live, you'll need to store vars in Vercel/System config.

# If not set, we provide default values (check `scaffold.config.ts`) so developers can start prototyping out of the box,
# but we recommend getting your own API Keys for Production Apps.

# To access values stored in this env file you can use: process.env.VARIABLENAME
# You'll need to prefix variables names with NEXT_PUBLIC_ if you want to access them on the client side.
# More info: https://nextjs.org/docs/pages/building-your-application/configuring/environment-variables

# Etherscan API Key for blockchain RPC and data access
# Get your free API key at: https://etherscan.io/apis
NEXT_PUBLIC_ETHERSCAN_API_KEY=""

# WalletConnect Project ID for wallet connection
# Get your project ID at: https://cloud.walletconnect.com/
NEXT_PUBLIC_WALLET_CONNECT_PROJECT_ID=""

# Note: Custom RPC URLs are configured in packages/nextjs/scaffold.config.ts
# You can modify the rpcOverrides object to use your preferred RPC provider
# Examples: Infura, QuickNode, Ankr, or any other public/private RPC endpoint